Alembic migration scripts for the Job Visualizer backend.

env.py wires DATABASE_URL (via src/backend/api/config.Settings) into Alembic
and targets the default alembic_version tracker. target_metadata points at
src/backend/api/db_models.Base. Table names are env-agnostic: every
environment uses bare names (job_listings, scrape_runs, users,
user_enabled_companies).

env.py also honors the PYTEST_SCHEMA env var: when set, it runs
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS "<schema>" + SET search_path TO "<schema>",
public on the Alembic connection so migrations land inside a per-worker
test schema instead of public. Production leaves PYTEST_SCHEMA unset.

The baseline revision 91337142414f (upgrade/downgrade are no-ops) exists
so prod can be `alembic stamp <baseline>` before the first Alembic-era
deploy. Revision e1974f8f8eee renames the pre-existing _{env}-suffixed
tables and indexes to their bare forms in a single RENAME-only migration;
see docs/implementations/envAgnosticTables/DEPLOY.md for the runbook.

Add a schema change:
  1. Edit src/backend/api/db_models.py
  2. cd src/backend && alembic revision --autogenerate -m "short message"
  3. Review the generated file — any multi-column ALTER on the same table
     must be one op.batch_alter_table(...) block, not N op.alter_column calls
     (per docs/incidents/2026-04-18-migration-filled-postgres-volume/volume-
     downgrade-playbook.md Rule 3).
  4. cd src/backend && alembic upgrade head
  5. Commit the revision file.
